  "texts": [
    "This pacing problem means \"AI for all\" may lack binding rules at the moment they're most needed.",
    "For example, the EU's effort to enact a comprehensive AI law (the EU AI Act) began in 2021 but is only reaching approval stages by 2024.",
    "Regulatory lag suggests that without adaptive, faster mechanisms, hard law will chronically catch up \"after the fact,\" struggling to address AI's latest challenges.",
    "Secondly, the abstract and non-binding nature of soft law facilitates easier adoption.",
    "Because they lack legal force, soft law measures face fewer political hurdlesno need for lengthy legislative votes or international treaties."
  ],
